## I/O Layer: plink2_text (already compiled)

We already compile these in our `pgenlib` static library:

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `plink2_text.cc` | TextStream: streaming line reader with decompression |
| `plink2_bgzf.cc` | BGZF decompression via libdeflate (faster than zlib) |
| `plink2_string.cc` | Optimized string scanning |
| `plink2_thread.cc` | Threading primitives for background decompression |

**TextStream API** (zero-copy, already available):
```cpp
textFILE txf;
TextFileOpen(path, &txf);       // opens file, auto-detects compression
char* line_start;
TextFileNextLine(&txf, &line_start);  // returns pointer into internal buffer
char* line_end = TextFileLineEnd(&txf);
CleanupTextFile(&txf, &reterr);
```

This gives us libdeflate BGZF decompression — the primary speed advantage
over htslib (which uses zlib).

**Limitation**: TextStream uses raw `FILE*`, not DuckDB VFS. Won't work with
S3/HTTP URIs. For Phase 1, local files only. DuckDB VFS fallback for remote
files is a future enhancement.

