## API Design

### Function: `read_vcf(path VARCHAR)`

| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |
|-----------|------|---------|-------------|
| `samples` | `ANY` | all | Subset by name or 0-based index |
| `region` | `VARCHAR` | none | `'chr:start-end'` filter |
| `variants` | `ANY` | all | Subset by ID or 0-based index |
| `genotypes` | `VARCHAR` | `'array'` | `'array'`, `'list'`, `'columns'` |
| `orient` | `VARCHAR` | `'variant'` | `'variant'`, `'genotype'`, `'sample'` |
| `phased` | `BOOLEAN` | `false` | Haplotype pair output |
| `vcf_half_call` | `VARCHAR` | `'missing'` | Half-call handling |
| `vcf_min_gq` | `INTEGER` | none | Min genotype quality filter |
| `vcf_min_dp` | `INTEGER` | none | Min read depth filter |

### Output schema

Same as `read_pgen` (variant orient default):
CHROM, POS, ID, REF, ALT, genotypes ARRAY(TINYINT, N)

